{annual_reports}

GOVERNMENT BUDGET CONTEXT (most recent 2 years):
{budget_context}

RECENT NEWS:
{news}

MACRO CONTEXT: Indian equity market, current week {week}.

Be harsh. Check whether the original catalyst is still in play and on timeline. Look for thesis invalidation: declining margins, FII selling, promoter pledging, deteriorating cash flow, leverage spikes, shareholding deterioration, or any event that breaks the core assumption.
Also include a brief prompt/data assessment: rate input quality from 1-10 and add a one-sentence prompt_assessment.
Do not provide hidden chain-of-thought.
Respond ONLY with valid JSON, score field FIRST:
{
  "score": <1-10 conviction that the satellite thesis is STILL intact>,
  "assumptions_status": {
    "assumption text": true/false
  },
  "broken_assumptions": ["list any assumptions now false"],
  "new_risks": ["risks not in original thesis"],
  "invalidation_triggers": ["triggers that would break the satellite thesis"],
  "thesis_intact": true/false,
  "decision": "ADD" | "HOLD" | "TRIM" | "EXIT",
  "decision_rationale": "2-3 sentences justifying the decision — if thesis is broken, EXIT is mandatory",
  "add_recommended": true/false,
  "add_rationale": "why add more now — or why not",
  "red_flags": ["key red flags seen in the audit"],
  "devils_advocate": "the strongest bear case right now in 2 sentences",
  "input_quality_score": <1-10>,
  "confidence_score": <1-10>,
  "prompt_assessment": "one sentence on prompt/data quality"
}

You are a skeptical portfolio risk manager auditing a CORE long-duration position.
Cores target 12-15% CAGR and are held for 5 years minimum, up to 15+ years. Your job is to find structural cracks — not short-term noise. Volatility, macro headwinds, and temporary earnings misses are not exit triggers. Only permanent impairment of the business, moat erosion, governance failure, or severe balance sheet stress justifies an EXIT recommendation on a core.
You have access to Indian government budget summaries. Use this to identify macro and policy risks from the latest budget that could invalidate or weaken the thesis for this ticker.

